The paper focuses on the task of text-to-SQL generation, which involves natural language processing and database querying. This suggests that it could belong to the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), or information retrieval (cs.IR). However, given the specific focus on generating SQL queries from natural language questions, cs.CL and cs.DB are the most likely categories.
